                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18310908-403-off2072 t18310908-403-crimeloc2074"></join>. On the 10th of September, the prisoner came on board and asked me for a job to paint; I did not know him before, but I set him to paint - there was no one on board but myself; I went below and heard him go to the fore part of the ship, where 
               <persName id="t18310908-403-person2878">
                  William 
                  Thornton
               <interp inst="t18310908-403-person2878" type="surname" value="Thornton"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310908-403-person2878" type="given" value="William"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310908-403-person2878" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            's chest was - I went up, and found the prisoner with his trousers loose and his shoes off; I asked what he was doing there, he said shaking the dirt off his clothes - I said it was a curious place to do that; he stopped a little time, and asked if he was to go to painting again - I then looked at a pair of trousers, which I saw him throw aside, and I saw they were Thornton's; I then went to look for the prisoner, and he was gone on shore - he looked very bulky, and I sent a boy to watch him.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18310908-403-person2879">
